{
  "text": "The detection theory developed in Ingster (1999) and [CITATION_1] provides a benchmark for a theory of consistent estimation. However, the theoretical analysis for estimation of the proportion contains further challenges that are not present in the detection problem. For example, the procedure in [CITATION_2] is only capable of estimating n consistently on a subset of the detectable region, failing to achieve the optimality benchmark of the detection boundary. [CITATION_3] developed an effective data-driven method for a two-point homoscedastic Gaussian mixture model Xi",
